---
const FAQs = [
  {
    question: "How is this different from other color tools?",
    answer:
      "Most tools give you a palette to look at. AlwanKit gives you a complete, production-ready color system, every role defined, dark mode included, accessible by default, exported as real code you can use immediately.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can I use my own brand color as the base?",
    answer:
      "Absolutely. That's exactly the point, drop in your brand's primary color and AlwanKit builds a full system around it, keeping your identity while filling in everything else.",
  },
  {
    question: "Are the generated colors actually accessible?",
    answer:
      "Yes. Every color is calculated to meet WCAG contrast standards automatically, light mode, dark mode, every role. You're not checking anything manually.",
  },
  {
    question: "What formats can I export in?",
    answer:
      "CSS, SCSS, Tailwind, and JSON. Pick the one your project already uses and drop it straight in.",
  },
  {
    question: "Is it open source?",
    answer:
      "Fully. The code is on GitHub, free to use in personal and commercial projects, fork it, modify it, self-host it, No restrictions.",
  },
];
---

<section ui-section="faq">
  <div class="head">
    <div class="headings">
      <div class="subtitle">
        <i class="hgi hgi-stroke hgi-bubble-chat-question"></i> FAQ
      </div>
      <h1 class="title">Quick answers</h1>
    </div>
    <p class="description">Just the things you probably want to know.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="core">
    <div ui-slot="accordion">
      {
        FAQs.map((faq) => (
          <div ui-slot="accordion-item">
            <label ui-slot="accordion-trigger">
              <i class="hgi hgi-stroke hgi-bubble-chat-question" />
              {faq.question}
              <input type="checkbox" name="my-accordion" />
            </label>
            <div ui-slot="accordion-content" role="region">
              <p>{faq.answer}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  [ui-section="faq"] {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--spacing-32);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);

    .head {
      display: flex;
      gap: var(--spacing-12);
      flex-direction: column;

      .headings {
        display: grid;
        gap: var(--spacing-8);

        .subtitle {
          font: var(--font-body-sm);
          border-radius: var(--radius-rounded);
          padding: var(--spacing-2) var(--spacing-8);
          background-color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
          box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
          display: flex;
          align-items: center;
          gap: var(--spacing-4);
          width: fit-content;

          & > i {
            color: var(--color-primary);
          }
        }

        .title {
          font: var(--font-headline-lg);
        }
      }

      .description {
        width: 80%;
        color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
      }
    }

    .core {
    }

    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;

      .head {
        .description {
          width: 100%;
        }
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 769px) {
      .head {
        .headings {
          .title {
            font: var(--font-title-lg);
          }
        }
      }

      .core {
      }
    }
  }
</style>
